1. Introduction

This Holonic Ownership Model Agreement ("HOM Agreement"), effective as of [Date], is entered into between [Company Name] ("the Company") and [Investor Name] ("the Investor"), collectively referred to as the "Parties."

2. Funding and Membership Interests

The Investor agrees to provide the Company with a capital infusion of $[________] ("Investment Amount") in exchange for future membership interests in the Company, subject to the terms set forth herein.

3. Valuation and Membership Interest Conversion

Valuation Cap: The post-money valuation cap is established at $[__________].

Membership Interest Conversion Events: The Investment Amount will convert into a membership interest percentage under the following circumstances:
Real Estate Closing: Upon the closing of the purchase of the designated property ("Property Closing"), the Investment Amount shall convert into a membership percentage. The percentage of membership interest received by the Investor will be calculated based on a valuation of $[__________] (or the actual appraised value of the property, if different) and the total capital contributions to the Company at the time of the Property Closing.

4. Dissolution Event

In the event of the Company's dissolution, winding up, liquidation, or reorganization, the Investor shall be entitled to receive a return of their Investment Amount prior to any distribution to members, subject to the rights of creditors and senior security holders.

5. Investor Rights

Information Rights: The Investor shall receive regular financial statements and other information concerning the financial status and operations of the Company.

Voting Rights: Upon conversion, the Investor shall have voting rights proportionate to their membership percentage in the Company.

Pre-emptive Rights: The Investor will have the right to participate pro-rata in future funding rounds to maintain their ownership percentage.

6. Representations and Warranties

Both the Company and the Investor make standard representations and warranties concerning authority, compliance with laws, and absence of conflicts or additional encumbrances that would impair the agreement.

7. Miscellaneous Provisions

Governing Law: This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of [State].

Amendments: Any amendments to this Agreement must be made in writing and signed by both parties.

Severability: If any provision of this Agreement is found to be unenforceable or invalid, that provision will be limited or eliminated to the minimum extent necessary so that this Agreement will otherwise remain in full force and effect and enforceable.

Entire Agreement: This Agreement is the complete and exclusive statement of the mutual understanding of the parties and supersedes all previous written and oral agreements, communications, and other understandings relating to the subject matter of this Agreement.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have executed this HOM Agreement as of the date first above written.

